Description:
Annotation on the envelope: "Rubens Italien 1600-1608"

  • Notes about S. Croce in Gerusalemme dated 1944
  • Bibliographic references
  • Extracts from different publications
  • Photos of part of 'The Gonzaga Family in Adoration of the Holy Trinity'
  • First subfolder (Annotation: "Mantua"):
    • Reproductions of 'The Gonzaga Family in Adoration of the Holy Trinity' and 'The transfiguration'
    • Photos of the Holy Trinity church in Mantua and sketches
    • Extracts from different publications
    • Draft text about the Holy Trinity church in Mantua and 'The Gonzaga Family in Adoration of the Holy Trinity'
    • Correspondence with Nino Giannantonj (Palazzo Ducale di Mantova) (dated 1937), with L. Burchard (dated 1937), with Hofrat (dated 1936)
  • Photos of "Die Altarbilder von Rubens für Il Gesú in Rom" by L. Burchard
  • Munich Library loan forms
  • Second subfolder (Annotation: "Italien Einzelbilder"):
    • Extracts from different publications
    • Reproductions of engravings of 'Saint George and the Dragon' and 'The Circumcision'
    • Brochure about Lodovico Caracci by H. Bodmer
  • Third subfolder (Annotation: "Kopien Italien 1600-1608"):
    • Reproduction of 'Isabella d'Este'
    • Extracts from different publications
    • Bibliographic references
    • Draft text about Rubens in Italy
  • Exams of the seminary about the 'Disputa of the Holy Sacrament'
